text: Honestly, if an interview process is so abstract that you need to take a course to be prepared for it, it must be so far from the reality of the job that it starts getting pointless.
If I would start asking people here to reverse a fucking binary tree on a whiteboard no one could do it. And that’s fine, cause you will never even do it
It’s like you ask a car mechanic to calculate the additional drag your car gets when you stick your head out of the window while doing a dount...
was reading somewhere, more and more code schools offer “technical interview” classes
Where does that lead? Only thing you are then testing is if people can repeat after a book or teacher...
It says shit about how well they will do their job

Best to ask a mechanic what a certain part does and where it belongs.
Tell them to call your API. If they start writing `new AsyncT…` you kick them out the door. Easy as that.
